*****************Bootstrap*************
Bootstrap is a framework HTML, CSS and js 

**************Types of container************
.container: which sets a max-width at each responsive Breakpoint
.container-fluid: which is width:100% at all breakpoints
.container-{breakpoint}: which is width:100% until the specified breakpoint

************Size of screen************
Breakpoint      Class infix     Dimensions
Xsmall          sm              <576px
Small           sm              >=576px
Medium          md              >=768
Large           lg              >=992px
ExtraLarge      Xl              >=1200px
ExtraExt large  xxl             >=1400px

*************Grid system***************
in bootstrap you have in line budget of 12points (Maybe because it can be diveise in 2)

col: column

To have the number of element per lines i am suppose to divise 12/{number of elements} then the result is place in the html code
    eg: col-md-6    means 12/2 = 6 so we have two elts per line for medium screen
        col-lg-4    means 12/3 = 4 so we have two elts per line for medium screen

NB: the scroll bar can affect the result you have in your viewport because it is include in the size when you reduce or increase the size of the viewport in your browser

col-lg-6: will divise the screen in two parts equal

**************Typographie************

************Forms*************
radio button: to make one choice at each time
checkbox button: to make multiple choice
switch button: to switch for true or false
input : to enter message
label : for the text of the input
toggle button: to have different style when click or not
range: to move circle on line to show step
Floating label: to flaot text inside the input
files input: to add file in form or multiple files
form grid : to display input twice in column or not
validation

*************Buttons****************
btn: for button
    eg: btn-lg : to put the button more nig and his content too
button outline: button with no color content
button disabled: to make button unclickable
button group: to have group of button (eg: for  )

************Images/ icons**************
bi: bootstrap icon

Q&A:
    Q:Quelle est la classe CSS à utiliser pour obtenir un container responsive à largeur fixe ? (c’est-à-dire qu’il y a une largeur fixe pour chaque catégorie de résolutions)
    A: container

    Q:Quelle est la classe CSS à utiliser pour obtenir un container qui prend toute la largeur ?
    A:container fluid

    Q:Quelles sont les classes CSS que je dois ajouter à mes éléments si je veux qu’ils soient disposés en 1 colonne sur téléphone, 3 colonnes sur tablette et 6 colonnes sur ordinateur?
    A:col-sm-4 and col-md-2

    Q:Quelle classe CSS doit-on utiliser pour obtenir une image en forme de rond (ou ellipse) ?
    A: rounded-circle

    Q:Quelles sont la ou les classes CSS à utiliser pour insérer une icône Bootstrap en forme de loupe (sur un bouton de recherche par exemple) ?
    A:bi and bi-search

